# public-surface-forbidden.regex — Arcanada-one/coworker
#
# Consumer regex file for the Public Surface Hygiene Mandate gate
# (Arcanada-one/datarim .github/workflows/public-surface-lint.yml, invoked
# from .github/workflows/public-surface.yml via `regex_file:`).
#
# public-surface-lint.sh takes a single regex file per invocation (one source
# of truth — see its own header comment), so this file duplicates the
# framework's neutral base patterns verbatim and appends coworker's own
# project-specific task-prefix pattern below, per the base file's documented
# consumer-extension convention.
#
# Base set (mirrors Arcanada-one/datarim dev-tools/public-surface-forbidden.regex):

\bPRD-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\bcreative-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\bplans-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\binsights-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\breflection-[A-Z]{2,10}-[0-9]{4}\b
\bdatarim/(tasks|creative|plans|insights|reflection)/
\b(M|Phase) ?[1-9][0-9]*\b

# Project-specific: internal Arcanada ecosystem task IDs (TUNE-tier backlog)
# must not leak into shipped OSS content — provenance stays in git log / the
# ecosystem backlog, never in a published README/CHANGELOG/docs page.
\bTUNE-[0-9]{4}\b
